<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align:center;"><font color="#FFFFFF">Holy Monasteries of Our Lady and Saint Laurence</font><br/><font color="#FFFFFF">Antiochian Orthodox Christian Archdiocese of North America,</font><br/><font color="#FFFFFF">Western Rite Vicariate</font></h2>

<div><div class="wsite-multicol"><div class="wsite-multicol-table-wrap" style="margin:0 -15px;">
	<table class="wsite-multicol-table">
		<tbody class="wsite-multicol-tbody">
			<tr class="wsite-multicol-tr">
				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:50.210970464135%; padding:0 15px;">
					
						

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:justify;"><br/><font size="3"><font color="#33ccff">The </font><em style="color:rgb(51, 204, 255)">Monasteries of Our Lady and Saint Laurence</em><font color="#33ccff"> belong to the Antiochian Orthodox Christian Archdiocese's Western-rite Vicariate, under the </font><em style="color:rgb(51, 204, 255)">omophorion </em><font color="#33ccff">of His Grace, Bishop John, Vicar Bishop.</font><br/><br/><font color="#33ccff">Founded on Holy Cross Day, 2013, the monasteries strive to model their life on the </font><em style="color:rgb(51, 204, 255)">Holy Rule</em><font color="#33ccff"> of Saint Benedict of Nursia (d. 547 A.D.), modified by their own&nbsp;</font><em style="color:rgb(51, 204, 255)">Constitutions</em><font color="#33ccff">, under the guidance of thier elected Abbot. After a period as a "community-in-formation," the monasteries were granted canonical status on July 16, 2015, by His Eminence, Metropolitan JOSEPH; as of February 1, 2018, they were formally identified as distinct Monasteries, one for men and one for women. While sharing some common facilities and living under one Abbot, the plan is for them to each develop their own identity as they grow and, eventually, to have separate facilities as numbers and finances allow.</font><br/><font color="#33ccff">&nbsp;<br/>&#8203;</font><br/><font color="#e0bf5c">We invite you to participate in our life and ministry by making a tax-deductible donation to the Monasteries using the Paypal button below. Thank you!</font></font><br/><br/><br/><br/></div>

