<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align:center;"><font color="#FFFFFF">St Benedict,<br/><span>"Father of Monks"</span></font></h2>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:justify;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<font color="#33CCFF" size="3">As a youth, St Benedict (d. 547 A.D.) embraced the life of a hermit before going on to found coenobitic monasteries and writing his <em>Rule</em>. He came to be considered the "Patriarch of Western Orthodox Monasticism.</font><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font color="#33CCFF" size="3">His life was made</font><font color="#33CCFF" size="3">&nbsp;known through the <em>Dialogues</em> of St Gregory the Great.<br/>&#8203;</font><br/></div>

<div style="text-align:center;"><div style="height: 10px; overflow: hidden;"></div>
<a class="wsite-button wsite-button-small wsite-button-normal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180404152547/http://www.osb.org/gen/greg/">
<span class="wsite-button-inner">Life of St Benedict</span>
</a>
<div style="height: 10px; overflow: hidden;"></div></div>


					
				</td>				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:31.345947460126%; padding:0 15px;">
					
						

<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align:center;"><font color="#FFFFFF">The Holy Rule,<br/>and More&nbsp;</font></h2>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:justify;"><font size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;<font color="#00CCCC">&nbsp;</font><font color="#33CCFF">&nbsp;A masterpiece of biblical, spiritual and psychological wisdom, the <em>Rule </em>of Saint Benedict dates from about 542 A.D.&nbsp;</font><br/><font color="#00CCCC"><font color="#66FFFF"><font color="#33CCFF">&nbsp;&nbsp; Once the revisions adopted in February of 2018 have been incorporated into them, you be able to access a large document that combines, thematically, the <em>Rule</em>, our <em>Constitutions</em>, and our <em>Customary</em>.</font></font></font></font></div>

<div style="text-align:center;"><div style="height: 10px; overflow: hidden;"></div>
<a class="wsite-button wsite-button-small wsite-button-normal" href="javascript:;">
<span class="wsite-button-inner">Under Revision</span>
</a>
<div style="height: 10px; overflow: hidden;"></div></div>


					
				</td>				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:34.678411500878%; padding:0 15px;">
					
						

<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align:center;"><font color="#FFFFFF">Daily Monastic Life<br/>at Our Lady&nbsp; &amp; St Laurence</font></h2>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:justify;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font color="#33CCFF" size="3">The life of our monastics is divided between times of solitude, worship, work, prayer, <em>lectio divina</em> (spiritual reading according to the ancient, Benedictine practice), and offering hospitality to the guests of the Retreat Center. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In addition, we engage in limited mission outreach such as preaching, retreats, prison visitation.</font></div>

<div style="text-align:center;"><div style="height: 10px; overflow: hidden;"></div>
<a class="wsite-button wsite-button-small wsite-button-normal" href="/web/20180404152547/http://www.saintlaurenceosb.org/uploads/3/4/5/3/34536971/monastic_horarium_ash_wed-_eve_of_palm_sunday.pdf">
<span class="wsite-button-inner">Daily Schedule</span>
</a>
<div style="height: 10px; overflow: hidden;"></div></div>


					
				</td>			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>
</div></div></div>

